        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 8:25PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 824 PM CDT/724 PM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm 13 miles southeast of Maljamar, or 20 miles southwest of
Lovington, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hobbs, Lovington, Monument, Nadine, Humble City, Knowles, Lea County
Regional Airport, and Industrial Airpark.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
